Bristol selector Dan Pearce is known
for his high-octane, party-starting DJ
style. He's pulled together music from
Matthew Herbert, Radio Slave, Mr. G,
Steve 'Silk' Hurley and Richie Hawtin
(as Robotman) for Fries With That?,
whose discs are titled Main Course and
Dessert. "These mixes have been a
labour of love for me, and something
that I really wanted to get across in
the right way," Pearce says. "Disc One
is a collection of records that I am
really feeling at the moment and hope
will stand the test of time as a mix CD
that you can listen to for years to
come, whilst Disc Two is basically a
collection of my classics, either
records I grew up with, ones that got
me into house/techno, or I have
discovered along the way and have
become classics to me, even if I have
only known them for a short while."

- Resident Advisor
